The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of rough sets for feature selection is a machine learning technique (cs.LG) that has been applied in various fields, including image processing. The paper also involves the selection of color channels, which is related to color-based image processing (cs.MM). The proposed approach can be seen as a form of feature selection for image retrieval (cs.IR) and can also be applied in other areas of computer vision, such as object recognition (cs.AI).
